(40, 1, 'Four Jobs Ready for ICT', 'XL AXIATA', '<p><strong>1. Engineer &ndash; Billing Development</strong><br />\r\nJob Roles:<br />\r\n- Check and implement configuration changes related to Product Catalogue and PCRF module correct and timely and also to ensure production deployment properly.<br />\r\n- Operate and produce testing execution and result related to modules Product and PCRF Catalogue to fulfill business/user requirements. To ensure all the PC changes configuration are correct and accurate in Production.<br />\r\n- Deliver configuration changes to Production within schedule&nbsp; to ensure its alignment with requirements<br />\r\n- Review configuration and implementation of related Product Catalogue and PCRF module to ensure revenue loss &le; 1%<br />\r\nRequirements:<br />\r\n- Minimum Bachelor Degree (S1) from Electrical Engineering or Information Technology/Computer Science with minimum 1 year working experience in related area, preferable in Telco industry<br />\r\n- Basic&nbsp; understanding of UNIX &amp; PL/SQL<br />\r\n- Basic understanding of Database, preferable Memory Database<br />\r\n- Basic Understanding/Knowledge in Billing System, preferably in billing telco<br />\r\n- Attention to detail<br />\r\n- Planning &amp; Organizing<br />\r\n- Communication &amp; coordination<br />\r\n- Result Oriented</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Engineer &ndash; Touchpoint &amp; Fulfillment</strong><br />\r\nJob Roles:<br />\r\n- Deliver Touchpoint &amp; Fulfillment related projects/solution within expected time to fulfill business requirement<br />\r\n- Perform unit testing and support internal test for every project delivered before internal testing by IT Tester to ensure the smoothness in Testing, Staging and Production environment<br />\r\n- Perform Incident Resolution on 3nd layer within SLA to achieve Customer Satisfaction<br />\r\n- Build handover document and do sharing session to operation and monitoring team<br />\r\n- Delivery quality, ensure the service working properly in Production<br />\r\n- Do assessment for project with small until medium impact to customer or service<br />\r\nRequirements:<br />\r\n- Academic Background: minimum S1 university graduate in a Telecommunication, Electro and Computer Engineering discipline from a reputable university<br />\r\n- have intermediate knowledge and technical skills on IT<br />\r\n- Basic Operating Systems (Sun Solaris, Unix, Windows, Linux)<br />\r\n- Java J2EE, PL/SQL, Unix,&nbsp; or other required intermediate programming language<br />\r\n- Enterprise Database System (Oracle)<br />\r\n- Understand ISO banking is an advantage<br />\r\n- Understand TIBCO product is an advantage<br />\r\n- Telco or Banking background is preferred<br />\r\n- Communication Skill<br />\r\n- Result oriented<br />\r\n- Attention to detail<br />\r\n- Quality and Customer oriented</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Engineer Production Support</strong><br />\r\nJob Roles:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n- Check and implement configuration changes related to following module : (1) Rating Amdocs&nbsp; Business Reference&nbsp; (CGI, Numbering, Short Code, POC, SGSN); (2) Roaming Partners for Out-Roamers (3) Change Offer Rule;&nbsp; (3) Default plan; (4) Non-Roaming; (5) Community ; (6) Bundling White list Management; (7) CLM Champaign; (8) SOA/R (9)UMB (10) SPM (11) CM, (12) RPL&nbsp; and other module to ensure production deployment<br />\r\n- Manage and Deploy Application System (SOA/R, Web,SPM) into production as agreed schedule<br />\r\n- Deliver configuration changes to Production within schedule&nbsp; to ensure its alignment with requirements<br />\r\n- Review configuration and implementation of related (1) Rating Amdocs&nbsp; Business Reference&nbsp; (CGI, Numbering, Short Code, POC, SGSN); (2) Roaming Partners for Out-Roamers (3) Change Offer Rule;&nbsp; (3) Default plan; (4) Non-Roaming; (5) Community ; (6) Bundling White list Management; (7) SOA/R Product ; (8) UMB (9) SPM (11) Q3, (12) CM, (13) RPL, , and other module to ensure revenue loss &le; 1%<br />\r\n- Manage and Implement Bulk Activities Changes such (Extend Active Period, Move Subscriber, Data Migration, Change Priceplan, Voucher Activation)<br />\r\nRequirements:<br />\r\n- S1 in Engineering : Electrical Engineering or Information System preferably<br />\r\n- Fresh graduate/1 year working experience preferable in Telco industry<br />\r\n- Basic&nbsp; understanding of UNIX &amp; PL/SQL<br />\r\n- Basic understanding of Database<br />\r\n- Basic Understanding/Knowledge in Billing System, preferably in billing telco<br />\r\n- Problem solving<br />\r\n- Communication &amp; coordination<br />\r\n- Team Work<br />\r\n- Attention to Detail<br />\r\n- Customer Orientation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Engineer IT Settlements</strong><br />\r\nJob Roles:<br />\r\n- Build, deliver and support the Settlement systems which are being used for financial settlement and revenue accounting purposes.<br />\r\n- Developing the solutions which processes the data from various sources and generate the reports and detail data<br />\r\n- Application support for the technical issues<br />\r\n- Application support for ad-hoc requirements<br />\r\n- Liaise with requirement managers, business users, designers, vendors to be able to deliver comprehensive solution<br />\r\n- Review the application and output data to ensure the quality of solution<br />\r\nRequirements:<br />\r\n- Degree in Computer Science/IT/Engineering, or equivalent years of experience.<br />\r\n- Minimum 3 years experience in development of Settlement/business-intelligence/data-warehousing/revenue-assurance area will be an advantage.<br />\r\n- Basic to intermediate knowledge in OSS source systems (Billing, CRM, ERP, card management etc).<br />\r\n- Basic to intermediate knowledge in Enterprise DBMS development (eg. Oracle PL/SQL) &amp; Unix Scripting.<br />\r\n- Basic to intermediate knowledge in ETL platform e.g. Data Stage/OWB/Ab-initio/other ETL tool.<br />\r\n- Basic to intermediate knowledge in Financial settlement, Business Intelligence &amp; data warehousing concepts, data and dimensional modeling, data quality principles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jika berminat bisa mengirimkan CV ke xlapp.diptyar@xl.co.id dengan subjek nama posisi yang dilamar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2016-01-21', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'Engineer – Billing Development, Engineer – Touchpoint &amp;amp; Fulfillment, etc.', 0),
